It started out as just tea time, but I couldn’t resist trying the crepes 😋 @little_choc
-
Can you believe everything in this spread is vegan and gluten free? Yeah, I’m shook too. This was my first vegan crepe and you could not tell it was vegan. Do yourself a favor and go get a burrito crepe. I can’t describe it well, but the sauce on the top was incredible. The crepe had all the smoky toasty savory flavors of a regular burrito- all in a vegan crepe.
-
my foodie friends will relate to my excitement when they pulled out edible flowers! I’ve been searching for edible flowers for my own pics at home, but I can never find them. This is the first time I got to play around with them :)

Creamsicle Crepe!

REVIEW: 👏 I actually made this lil guy at work, and it definitely made for a light dessert! A nice citrus tang with the orange slices and lemon juice paired nicely with the amazing clotted cream we have there, along with sliced almonds. Definitely a delicious sweet if you’re ever by the willy b neighborhood!

Stopped by @little_choc this weekend for a delicious beet/cucumber/pineapple juice and a delicious burrito inspired savory crepe filled with avocado, coconut bacon, cashew cheese, black beans, and hot sauce!
🌱 
Little Choc is completely GF (except for two beers they have) and vegan too!
🌱
I felt super safe picking up food thanks to their wonderful open window in the front and strict distancing and sanitization efforts in place.
🌱
Have you been here before? Would you go for a savory or sweet crepe? Let me know below!

Happy Friday! 🙌🎉 Here's my crepe from @little_choc in Brooklyn where the ambience is really cozy and the staff are super cheerful 😀  This one had bananas, homemade chocolate sauce, caramel, and clotted cream.  It was good overall with the bonus of being gluten free 👏  I'd just say that I prefer a thicker chocolate sauce -- melted chocolate basically -- but this had nice flavor.  Also next time I'll ask whether they can cook the bananas more to make them softer ;)

Who else’s jaw dropped after seeing this photo? 😱 From crepes and cookies to scones and smoothie bowls, the brunch at @little_choc does not disappoint! 😍⁠
